

China reported rising number of entries and exits in the third quarter of this year, with that of foreign nationals up 16.1 percent year-on-year to 10.63 million.

The number of entries and exits of Chinese mainland people amounted to 16.51 million in the third quarter, up 7 percent.

And entries and exits by Hong Kong and Macao residents rose by 8.9 percent to 49.76 million and the figure of Taiwan residents increased by 9 percent to 2.25 million, according to a briefing made by the Ministry of Public Security Thursday.

